abstract: If combat is the sincerest form of flattery in politics, Pete Buttigieg had some reason to be flattered on the Atlanta stage.

lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg was trying a little tenderness.

abstract: The candidates mostly tempered their criticism of one another and presented a united front on vital issues like climate change.
snippet: The candidates mostly tempered their criticism of one another and presented a united front on vital issues like climate change.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential candidates yielded to the furor surrounding the impeachment inquiry in Washington in their primary debate on Wednesday, for the first time training their fire more steadily on President Trump than on one another and presenting a largely united front on vital issues like climate change and abortion rights.

abstract: Mr. Messam, the mayor of Miramar, Fla., was trying to do what nobody has ever done: get elected president straight from a mayorship. But his campaign barely registered.
snippet: Mr. Messam, the mayor of Miramar, Fla., was trying to do what nobody has ever done: get elected president straight from a mayorship. But his campaign barely registered.
lead_paragraph: Wayne Messam, the mayor of Miramar, Fla., has ended a presidential campaign that barely got off the ground.

abstract: Car culture has already been changed by bike and bus lanes. A transportation panel in Manhattan has floated the idea of eliminating free street parking entirely.
snippet: Car culture has already been changed by bike and bus lanes. A transportation panel in Manhattan has floated the idea of eliminating free street parking entirely.
lead_paragraph: For drivers, finding a parking spot in New York City is already hard enough. There are so many regulations. So many hydrants. So many loading zones. And so few empty spaces.
